# Agent Memory Bootstrap

This file ships the convention layout for an adopting
repo's agent-facing working memory. Adopted repos should
copy this template (via `scripts/init.sh`) and check the
contents in at session start.

For the contract: see
[`core/agent-memory.md`](core/agent-memory.md) in the
framework.

## Layout

```
.agent-stack/
├── agent-notes/         # working memory, often gitignored
│   ├── current-task.md
│   ├── open-questions.md
│   └── investigation-log.md
└── agent-checkpoints/   # durable state, optionally committed
    ├── state.md
    ├── decisions.md
    └── experiences.md
```

The dotted directory keeps the memory unlisted by default
in most file trees. Adopters who prefer a non-dotted
name can rename `.agent-stack/agent-notes/` to
`docs/agents/agent-notes/` without changing the
convention's contract.

## Per-file template

### `agent-notes/current-task.md`

```markdown
# Current task

<!-- One paragraph: what the agent is doing right now,
     the slice plan, the success criterion. -->

Started: <YYYY-MM-DD>
Session: <arbitrary agent-side identifier>
Refs: <issue/PR/ADR>
```

### `agent-notes/open-questions.md`

```markdown
# Open questions

<!-- One line each. The agent owes the user a call on
     these before the slice can land. -->

- [ ] <question>: <why it's blocking>
- [x] <resolved question>: <answer + source>
```

### `agent-notes/investigation-log.md`

```markdown
# Investigation log

<!-- Append-only. Each entry is a brief context dump the
     agent relies on at session start. -->

## <YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM>
- Files opened: <paths>
- Tests run: <commands>
- Found: <one-line>
```

### `agent-checkpoints/state.md`

```markdown
# State

Last updated: <YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM>

## In flight
- <slice>: <status, e.g. "red tests in pkg/foo.go:42">

## Last green
- <slice + commit>: <short SHA>

## Blockers
- <blocker>: <who owns the unblock, when unblock is
  expected, link to relevant thread>

## Next actions
- [ ] <next slice or follow-up>
- [ ] <user-side decision needed>
```

### `agent-checkpoints/decisions.md`

```markdown
# Decisions

<!-- One per row. Each cites its source: PR, ADR, chat
     thread, or commit. Append-only. -->

| Decision | Source | Date |
|---|---|---|
| <one-sentence> | <link> | <YYYY-MM-DD> |
```

### `agent-checkpoints/experiences.md`

```markdown
# Experiences

<!-- Bugs the agent hit that the next agent must not
     re-discover. Append-only. Each entry: symptom, why,
     fix. -->

## <YYYY-MM-DD>: <slug>
**Symptom:** <one line>
**Why:** <file:line + one-line mechanism>
**Fix:** <the change that resolved it>
**Cite:** <issue/ADR/commit>

```

## Adopting

The `scripts/init.sh` script Q5 does not yet create this
directory; until Slice 2 ships that hook, create the
layout manually:

```bash
mkdir -p .agent-stack/agent-notes .agent-stack/agent-checkpoints
# Add .agent-stack/agent-notes/ to .gitignore
# Create the per-file templates above
```

The convention is unenforceable without the directory
existing; the templates above are what the agent reads
when it sits down at a fresh session.

